        <mxCell id="msg" value="A detection cell spans &#8216;stride&#8217; pixels. A ~12 px human is a fraction of one P5 or P4 cell &#8211; that cell must localize a sub-cell target amid 16&#8211;32 px of surrounding context &#8211; but spans about three P2 cells, enough to be localized precisely. This is why the added stride-4 (P2) head resolves targets the standard P3&#8211;P5 scales miss." style="text;html=1;fontFamily=Times New Roman;fontSize=10;align=left;verticalAlign=top;whiteSpace=wrap;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="30" y="300" width="740" height="46" as="geometry" /></mxCell>
